{{Infobox sports season | title = 2014 Netball Superleague season | league = [[Netball Superleague]] | sport = [[Netball]] | logo = | pixels = | no_of_teams = 8 | attendance = | average_attendance = | TV = | season = 2014 Netball Superleague season | season_champs = [[Manchester Thunder]] | season_champ_name= Champions | second_place= [[Surrey Storm]] | minor_premiers= | MVP = | top_scorer = | seasonslist = | seasonslistnames = | prevseason_link = 2013 Netball Superleague season | prevseason_year = 2013 | nextseason_link = 2015 Netball Superleague season | nextseason_year = 2015 }}
The '''2014 Netball Superleague season''' was the ninth season of the [[Netball Superleague]], the elite domestic [[netball]] competition in the [[United Kingdom]].
== Overview ==
===Format=== The three-phased format of the last [[2013 Netball Superleague season|two seasons]] was dropped and instead the league reverted to a double [[Round-robin tournament|round-robin]] format. After each team played each other twice (once at home and once away), the top four teams qualified for the semi-finals, with the winners of those matches meeting in the Grand Final.<ref name=SCORE112>{{cite web|url=https://www.netballscoop.com/old/forums/topic/znsl-squads-2014/index.html|work=Netball Scoop Archive|date=13 January 2014|title=2014 Zeo Netball Superleague}}</ref><ref name=SCORE2>{{cite web|url=https://www.scoreboard.com/en/netball/united-kingdom/superleague-2014/|title=Netball: Superleague 2014 Results|work=scoreboard.com}}</ref>
===Teams=== The same eight teams as the previous season competed.
