{{Infobox organization |name = Bursa Büyükşehir Belediyesi Spor Kulübü |image = |image_border = |size = 150px |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |map2 = |abbreviation = Bursa B.B. SK |motto = |formation = {{Start date|1980}} |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = Sport: Athletics, basketball, chess, cue sports, cycling, gymnastics, karate, kayaking, sailing, scouting, shooting and hunting, swimming, table tennis, tennis, volleyball, water polo, wrestling |headquarters = |location = [[Bursa]], [[Turkey]] |coords = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> |region_served = |membership = |language = |general = |leader_title = President |leader_name = Recep Altepe (City mayor) |leader_title2 = Director |leader_name2 = Taha Başparmak |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |budget = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |website = {{URL|http://www.bursabbspor.com/}} |remarks = |former name = }} {{Bursa B.B. SK sections}}
'''Bursa Büyükşehir Belediyesi Spor Kulübü''', also known as '''Bursa Büyükşehir Belediyespor''' or simply '''Bursa B.B. SK''', is a Turkish [[Sports club|multi-sport]] club sponsored by the Metropolitan Municipality of [[Bursa]] in [[Turkey]].
Established in 1980 with five sports departments, Bursa Büyükşehir Belediye SK are currently active in 17 sports genres performed by around 5,000 licensed athletes. The club focuses on infrastructure.<ref name="bbbh">{{cite web |url=http://www.bursabbspor.com/kurumsal/hakkimizda |publisher=Bursa BBSpor |title=Hakkımızda |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-03-13 }}</ref>
The club has dedicated facilities available such as a table tennis hall, a wrestling hall as well as indoor and open-air tennis courts and swimming pools, which are also open to the public. Its Acemler Sports Hall hosts basketball, volleyball and karate events.<ref name="bbbh"/>
The women's basketball team plays in the Turkish Women's Basketball Second League<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bursabbspor.com/basarilarimiz/basketbol |publisher=Bursa BBSpor |title=Basketbol |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-03-13 }}</ref> and the [[Bursa B.B. Women's Volleyball|women's volleyball team]] competes in the [[Turkish Women's Volleyball League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bursabbspor.com/basarilarimiz/voleybol |publisher=Bursa BBSpor |title=Voleybol |language=Turkish |accessdate=2013-03-13 }}</ref>
The club's women's table tennis team consisting of Elena Dubkova (BLR), Sibel Ismail Remzi (TUR), Anamaria Sebe (ROM), Aylin Öztürk (TUR), Özge Şener (TUR) and Filiz Bozkurt (TUR) competed at the 2012-2013 Women's [[European Table Tennis Union|ETTU]] Cup.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ettu.org/womens-ettu-cup/clubs/ |publisher=ETTU |title=2012-2013 Women's ETTU Cup - Teams |accessdate=2013-03-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119050324/http://www.ettu.org/womens-ettu-cup/clubs/ |archivedate=2012-11-19 |df= }}</ref> In the Group C, they won against USD Tennistavola Zeus from [[Italy]] (3-1), losing however to the [[Austria]]n TTC Carinthiawinds-Villacher (1-3) and [[Russia]]n KFU Kazan (0-3) in the second round failing to advance to the third round.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ettu.org/lss/clubs2013/wettu-archive.php |publisher=ETTU |title=2012/2013 ETTU Club Competitions 's Live Scoring |accessdate=2013-03-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130315105822/http://www.ettu.org/lss/clubs2013/wettu-archive.php |archivedate=2013-03-15 |df= }}</ref> [[File:OTOGAR BUS STATION BUYUKSEHIR TURKEY OCT 2011 (6394664489).jpg|left|thumb|200px|Club logo at a bus station]]
