{{Infobox stadium | name = Estadio Enrique Torres Belón | nickname = | image = Estadio Enrique Torres Belón.jpg | fullname = Estadio Enrique Torres Belón | former names = | location = [[Puno]], [[Peru]] | coordinates = {{coord|-15.83691|-70.022028}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | renovated = | expanded = | owner = | operator = | dimensions = 105 × 70 m | surface = grass | capacity = 20,000 | tenants = [[Alfonso Ugarte de Puno|Alfonso Ugarte]] }}
'''Estadio Enrique Torres Belón''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Puno]], [[Peru]]. It is currently used by [[football (soccer)|football]] team [[C.D. Alfonso Ugarte|Alfonso Ugarte]]. The stadium is built out of stone and has a capacity of 20,000 people. It is named after Senator Enrique Torres Belón from the [[Puno Region]]. The stadium is also the site of the [[Fiesta de la Candelaria]] every February.
