'''Friedrich Gerhard''' (24 July 1884 &ndash; 16 May 1950) was a [[Germany|German]] [[equestrianism|equestrian]] and Olympic champion. He won two Olympic medals at the [[1936 Summer Olympics]] in Berlin.<ref name=sports-ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ge/friedrich-gerhard-1.html |title=Friedrich Gerhard |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=SR/Olympic Sports |accessdate=27 December 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329150301/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ge/friedrich-gerhard-1.html |archivedate=29 March 2010 |df= }}</ref>

